content.thinking:
The user wants me to continue fixing the centering issue. Looking at the CSS, I can see the issue:

In `index.css`, the body has:
```css
body {
  margin: 0;
  display: flex;
  place-items: center;
  min-width: 320px;
  min-height: 100vh;
}
```

This uses `place-items: center` which should center items, but there's no `justify-content: center` to horizontally center the content. The `place-items` shorthand sets both `align-items` and `justify-items`, but for flexbox, `justify-items` is ignored - you need `justify-content` for the main axis.

So the login screen is vertically centered but not horizontally centered. I need to add `justify-content: center` to the body styles.

Let me fix this.

